PT-BR

Algoritmo simples de cache LRU (Least Recently Used), ou seja, quando o cache está cheio, remove a chave menos utilizada.

Evitei o uso de HashTable, embora ela seja ideal para identificar e buscar os nós de forma mais otimizada (O(1)), mas quis forçar o estudo do Doubly Linked List.

Em uma aplicação real, o uso de HashTable em conjunto com o Doubly Linked List seria o mais recomendado.


EN

Simple LRU (Least Recently Used) cache algorithm, meaning, when the cache is full, it removes the least used key.

I avoided using a HashTable, even though it is ideal for identifying and searching nodes more efficiently (O(1)), but I wanted to focus on studying the Doubly Linked List.

In a real application, using a HashTable in conjunction with a Doubly Linked List would be most recommended.

